<font size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Update 2/12/2004</font><font size="2"> - 02-15-2004 10:16</font><br><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="100%"><font size="2">Tribute Update <br><br>The Tribute system as it was released has caused a greater variance in favor distribution than was intended. In order to make the system more healthy, fair, and balanced, there will be changes made over two updates -- one today and one next week. <br><br>The following changes have been made today: <br><br>- Favor Maximum: There will be a maximum limit of 200,000 favor that a player character can have available at any time. If a player has accumulated more than 200,000 favor at the time of this change, the character will retain its favor, but will not be able to add to it until it falls below 200,000. <br><br>- Favor Value Adjustments to Items: Some items have had their favor value adjusted to be more appropriate. For this update, this will not affect the favor amount that a player has gained by handing in items that have had their favor values adjusted. <br><br>For next week&#39;s update, we will be adjusting each character&#39;s favor amounts based on any items that were handed in to Tribute Masters that have had their favor values adjusted. <br><br>We hope you continue to enjoy the benefits of the Tribute system and Gates of Discord. <br><br>In other words: Play, raid and be merry, for tomorrow we nerf. </font><br><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="100%"><font size="2">- <a href="mailto:ronaldor@magecompendium.com">Ronaldor Vladimir</a></font><br><br></td>
</tr>
